# MeteoScientific Tutorial Website

This is a tutorial website teaching non-technical people how to use a custom Chirpstack LNS called MeteoScientific (MetSci). The site is built with Docusaurus and deployed via GitHub Actions to Vercel.

## Key Information
- **Purpose**: Educational tutorials for MeteoScientific LoRaWAN platform
- **Target Audience**: Non-technical users learning LoRaWAN and IoT
- **Technology Stack**: Docusaurus, React, GitHub Actions, Vercel
- **Repository**: https://github.com/gristlekinginc/metsci-site-v2
- **Development Environment**: Primarily Linux (Monstra) via Cursor on Mac

## Main Content Areas
- **Tutorials**: Step-by-step guides in [docs/tutorial-basics](mdc:docs/tutorial-basics) and [docs/tutorial-extras](mdc:docs/tutorial-extras)
- **Blog**: Industry articles and technical posts in [blog/](mdc:blog)
- **Codecs**: Device codec documentation in [docs/codecs](mdc:docs/codecs)
- **Components**: Reusable React components in [src/components](mdc:src/components)

